<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6168</anchor> <rss>erct-0006.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0006</addr>  <route>erct-0006.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Displayed category</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>displayed category</strong></em> is defined to be a <link href="erct-0004.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0004" title="Univalent displayed precategory">univalent</link> <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6169</anchor> <rss>erct-0005.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-0005</addr>  <route>erct-0005.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Displayed categories</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6170</anchor> <rss>erct-0001.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0001</addr>  <route>erct-0001.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date><date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Displayed precategory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>displayed precategory</strong></em> <tex>C</tex> over a <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>B</tex>, written <tex>B \vdash  C</tex>, is specified by the following data:</p><ol><li>for each <tex>b \in  B</tex>, a type <tex>\left \lvert C \right \rvert b</tex> of <em>displayed objects</em> over <tex>b</tex> that we shall write <tex>b.c \in  C</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>b_0.c_0, b_1.c_1 \in  C</tex> and <tex>i \colon  b_0 \to  b_1</tex>, a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link> <tex>C  _{ i } \mathopen {} \left ( b_0.c_0 , b_1.c_1 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> of <em>displayed arrows</em> over <tex>i</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>b.c \in  C</tex> a displayed <em>identity arrow</em> <tex>1_{ b } . 1_{ c } \colon  b.c \to  b.c</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>i.f \colon  b_0.c_0 \to  b_1.c_1</tex> and <tex>j.g \colon  b_1.c_1 \to  b_2.c_2</tex>, a displayed <em>composite arrow</em> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( j \circ  i \right ) \mathclose {} \circ \mathopen {} \left ( g \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {} \colon  b_0.c_0  \to  b_1.c_1</tex>;</li>
  <li>such that composition is associative and unital with respect to displayed identity arrows.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6171</anchor> <rss>erct-0002.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0002</addr>  <route>erct-0002.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Vertical displayed arrow</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given two displayed objects <tex>b.c,b.c'</tex> in a <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex>, we shall refer to displayed arrows of the form <tex>1_{ b } .f \colon  b.c \to  b.c'</tex> as <em><strong>vertical</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6172</anchor> <rss>erct-0003.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0003</addr>  <route>erct-0003.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber of a displayed precategory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> be a <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link>. We define the <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of <tex>C</tex> over <tex>b \in  B</tex> to be the <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>b.C</tex> whose objects are given by displayed objects <tex>b.c \in  C</tex> and whose arrows <tex>b.c_0 \to  b.c_1</tex> are given by <link href="erct-0002.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0002" title="Vertical displayed arrow">vertical displayed arrows</link> <tex>1_{ b } .f \colon  b.c_0 \to  b.c_1</tex>, with identities and compositions inherited from <tex>C</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6173</anchor> <rss>erct-0004.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0004</addr>  <route>erct-0004.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Univalent displayed precategory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> is called <em><strong>univalent</strong></em> when each of its <link href="erct-0003.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0003" title="Fiber of a displayed precategory">fiber precategories</link> <tex>b.C</tex> is <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6174</anchor> <rss>erct-0007.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0007</addr>  <route>erct-0007.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Total (pre)category</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>total (pre)category</strong></em> <tex>B.C</tex> of a <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> is defined so that <tex>\left \lvert B.C \right \rvert</tex> is the type <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( b \in  B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( b \in  B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( b \in  B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( b \in  B \right ) \mathclose {} } } \left \lvert C \right \rvert b</tex> of displayed objects of <tex>C</tex> and <tex>B.C \mathopen {} \left ( b.c , b'.c' \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is the type of displayed morphisms <tex>i.f \colon  b.c \to  b'.c'</tex> in <tex>C</tex>, with identities and compositions inherited from <tex>C</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6175</anchor> <rss>erct-000A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000A</addr>  <route>erct-000A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Display functor</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given a <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex>, we may define a functor <tex>\pi _{ B \vdash  C } \colon  B.C \to  B</tex> called the <em><strong>display functor</strong></em>, sending <tex>b.c  \in  B.C</tex> to <tex>b</tex> and <tex>i.f \colon  b.c \to  b'.c'</tex> to <tex>i \colon  b \to  b'</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6176</anchor> <rss>erct-0008.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0008</addr>  <route>erct-0008.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Conditions for the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> to be <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> be a  <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> displayed over a  <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>B</tex>. If <tex>B</tex> is <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link> and <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> is <link href="erct-0004.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0004" title="Univalent displayed precategory">univalent</link>, then the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <tex>B.C</tex> is univalent.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6177</anchor> <rss>erct-0009.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Exercise</taxon> <addr>erct-0009</addr>  <route>erct-0009.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">Univalence</link> of the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <em>vs.</em> the <link href="erct-0003.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0003" title="Fiber of a displayed precategory">fibers</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Give an example of a <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> over a  <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>B</tex> such that the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <tex>B.C</tex> is <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link> but <tex>B</tex> is nonetheless not <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6178</anchor> <rss>erct-000R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000R</addr>  <route>erct-000R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>8</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Vertical displayed functor</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B \vdash  C,D</tex> be two <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategories</link>. A <em><strong>vertical displayed functor</strong></em> from <tex>C</tex> to <tex>D</tex> over <tex>B</tex>, written <tex>B.F  \colon  C \to  D</tex>, is given by the following data:</p><ol><li>
    for each displayed object <tex>b.c \in  C</tex>, a displayed object <tex>b.Fc  \in  D</tex>;
  </li>
  <li>
    for each displayed arrow <tex>i.f \colon  b_0.c_0  \to  b_1.c_1</tex> in <tex>C</tex>, a displayed arrow <tex>i.Ff \colon  b_0.Fc_0 \to  b_1.Fc_1</tex> in <tex>D</tex>;
  </li>
  <li>such the assignment of displayed arrows preserves displayed identities and displayed composites.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6179</anchor> <rss>erct-000S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000S</addr>  <route>erct-000S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>8</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Vertical displayed natural transformation</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B.F, B.G \colon  C \to  D</tex> be two <link href="erct-000R.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000R" title="Vertical displayed functor">vertical displayed functors</link> between two <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategories</link> <tex>B \vdash  C,D</tex>. A <em><strong>vertical displayed natural transformation</strong></em> from <tex>B.F</tex> to <tex>B.G</tex> over <tex>B</tex>, written <tex>B. \alpha \colon  B.F \to  B.G</tex>, is given by the following data:</p><ol><li>
    for each displayed object <tex>b.c \in  C</tex>, a <link href="erct-0002.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0002" title="Vertical displayed arrow">vertical arrow</link> <tex>b. \alpha _c \colon  b.Fc \to  b.Gc</tex>;
  </li>
  <li>
    such that the following naturality law holds for all <link href="erct-0002.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0002" title="Vertical displayed arrow">vertical</link> <tex>b.f  \colon  b.c_0 \to  b.c_1</tex> in <tex>b.C</tex>:
    
 
  
  
    <center><img src="resources/2bc2d8e73aa29d06dec5e9042dee463e.svg"/></center>
  </li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><p>The material on displayed categories is drawn from <link href="ahrens-lumsdaine-2019.xml" type="local" addr="ahrens-lumsdaine-2019" title="Displayed categories">Ahrens and Lumsdaine</link>, although we have imposed our own terminological and notational conventions.</p></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6180</anchor> <rss>erct-0001.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0001</addr>  <route>erct-0001.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date><date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Displayed precategory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>displayed precategory</strong></em> <tex>C</tex> over a <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>B</tex>, written <tex>B \vdash  C</tex>, is specified by the following data:</p><ol><li>for each <tex>b \in  B</tex>, a type <tex>\left \lvert C \right \rvert b</tex> of <em>displayed objects</em> over <tex>b</tex> that we shall write <tex>b.c \in  C</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>b_0.c_0, b_1.c_1 \in  C</tex> and <tex>i \colon  b_0 \to  b_1</tex>, a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link> <tex>C  _{ i } \mathopen {} \left ( b_0.c_0 , b_1.c_1 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> of <em>displayed arrows</em> over <tex>i</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>b.c \in  C</tex> a displayed <em>identity arrow</em> <tex>1_{ b } . 1_{ c } \colon  b.c \to  b.c</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>i.f \colon  b_0.c_0 \to  b_1.c_1</tex> and <tex>j.g \colon  b_1.c_1 \to  b_2.c_2</tex>, a displayed <em>composite arrow</em> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( j \circ  i \right ) \mathclose {} \circ \mathopen {} \left ( g \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {} \colon  b_0.c_0  \to  b_1.c_1</tex>;</li>
  <li>such that composition is associative and unital with respect to displayed identity arrows.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6181</anchor> <rss>erct-0004.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0004</addr>  <route>erct-0004.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Univalent displayed precategory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> is called <em><strong>univalent</strong></em> when each of its <link href="erct-0003.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0003" title="Fiber of a displayed precategory">fiber precategories</link> <tex>b.C</tex> is <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6182</anchor> <rss>erct-000O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Observation</taxon> <addr>erct-000O</addr>  <route>erct-000O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>7</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000H" title="Category">Categories</link> as <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed categories</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> over the terminal category gives precisely the data of a <link href="erct-000H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000H" title="Category">category</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6183</anchor> <rss>erct-000N.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-000N</addr>  <route>erct-000N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>7</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Relative displayed categories</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The purpose of <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed categories</link> is to define category-like objects that depend on other categories. We will later on learn how to impose conditions that make displayed categories behave like (potentially large) categories <em>internal</em> to other categories. In order to make the theory sufficiently flexible, however, it is necessary to first relativise the notion of displayed category to allow the base to be another (relative) displayed category rather than an ordinary category. The starting point of our approach to relativisation is the insight that a <link href="erct-000H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000H" title="Category">category</link> is a special case of <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link>.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6184</anchor> <rss>erct-000O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Observation</taxon> <addr>erct-000O</addr>  <route>erct-000O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>7</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000H" title="Category">Categories</link> as <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed categories</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> over the terminal category gives precisely the data of a <link href="erct-000H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000H" title="Category">category</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>In light of the <link href="erct-000O.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000O" title="Categories as displayed categories">observation above</link>, the base of a <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> in the sense that we have described so far is another <link href="etct-0006" type="external">displayed category</link> — whose base is the terminal category. This suggests a simple way to expand our vocabulary to account for <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed categories</link> whose base is another <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link>.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6185</anchor> <rss>erct-000P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000P</addr>  <route>erct-000P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>7</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Relative displayed category</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> over a precategory <tex>B</tex>. A  <em><strong>relative displayed precategory</strong></em> over <tex>C</tex>, written <tex>C \vdash  E</tex>, is defined to be a <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B.C \vdash  E</tex> over the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <tex>B.C</tex>. A <em><strong>relative displayed category</strong></em> over <tex>C</tex> is then a <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> over <tex>B.C</tex>.</p><p>When it is clear from context what we mean, we will speak of <em>displayed categories</em> over <tex>C</tex>, as in what follows, the relative version of displayed categories will be the primary one.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6186</anchor> <rss>erct-000Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Q</addr>  <route>erct-000Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>8</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The relative displayed precategory of slices</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> be a displayed precategory; we may define a <link href="erct-000P.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000P" title="Relative displayed category"><em>relative</em> displayed precategory</link> <tex>C \vdash   C  _{/}</tex> as follows:</p><ol><li>
    A displayed object <tex>b.c.p \in   C  _{/}</tex> is given by a <link href="erct-0002.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0002" title="Vertical displayed arrow">vertical arrow</link> over <tex>b \in  B</tex> with codomain <tex>b.c</tex>, i.e. an arrow <tex>p \colon   \partial _0 p \to  c</tex> in the <link href="erct-0003.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0003" title="Fiber of a displayed precategory">fiber precategory</link> <tex>b.C</tex>.
  </li>
  <li>
    Given displayed objects <tex>b_0.c_0.p_0, b_1.c_1.p_1 \in   C  _{/}</tex>, a displayed arrow <tex>i.f. \alpha \colon  b_0.c_0.p_0 \to  b_1.c_1.p_1</tex> in <tex>C  _{/}</tex> is given by a displayed arrow <tex>i. \alpha \colon  b_0. \partial _0p_0  \to  b_1. \partial _0 p_1</tex> in <tex>B.C</tex> making the following square commute:
    
 
  
  
    <center><img src="resources/74e1d98636b3c750245a96ea21c616e4.svg"/></center>
  </li>
  <li>
    For a displayed object <tex>b.c.p \in C  _{/}</tex>, the displayed identity arrow <tex>1_{ b } . 1_{ c } . 1_{ p }   \colon  b.c.p \to  b.c.p</tex> is given by the following square:
    
 
  
  
    <center><img src="resources/5ba67055e5267158c98f53a7f2ef710d.svg"/></center>
  </li>
  <li>
    The displayed composite of two displayed arrows <tex>i.f. \alpha   \colon  b_0.c_0.p_0  \to  b_1.c_1.p_1</tex> and <tex>j.g. \beta \colon  b_1.c_1.p_1 \to  b_2.c_2.p_2</tex> is given by the upstairs displayed composite in  <tex>B.C</tex> depicted below:
    
 
  
  
    <center><img src="resources/bf53704db36fbab793fbc32a2c64768a.svg"/></center>
  </li></ol></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6187</anchor> <rss>erct-000P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000P</addr>  <route>erct-000P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>7</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Relative displayed category</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> over a precategory <tex>B</tex>. A  <em><strong>relative displayed precategory</strong></em> over <tex>C</tex>, written <tex>C \vdash  E</tex>, is defined to be a <link href="erct-0001.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0001" title="Displayed precategory">displayed precategory</link> <tex>B.C \vdash  E</tex> over the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <tex>B.C</tex>. A <em><strong>relative displayed category</strong></em> over <tex>C</tex> is then a <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> over <tex>B.C</tex>.</p><p>When it is clear from context what we mean, we will speak of <em>displayed categories</em> over <tex>C</tex>, as in what follows, the relative version of displayed categories will be the primary one.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>6188</anchor> <rss>erct-0009.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Exercise</taxon> <addr>erct-0009</addr>  <route>erct-0009.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">Univalence</link> of the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <em>vs.</em> the <link href="erct-0003.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0003" title="Fiber of a displayed precategory">fibers</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Give an example of a <link href="erct-0006.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0006" title="Displayed category">displayed category</link> <tex>B \vdash  C</tex> over a  <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>B</tex> such that the <link href="erct-0007.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0007" title="Total (pre)category">total precategory</link> <tex>B.C</tex> is <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link> but <tex>B</tex> is nonetheless not <link href="erct-000D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000D" title="Univalent precategory">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>